-- StanChart monitoring situation at China's Qingdao port 
-- By Melanie Burton
-- Wed Jun 04, 2014 11:11PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, June 5 (Reuters) - Standard Chartered <STAN.L> said on Thursday it was monitoring events at Qingdao port, where a probe into metal financing has disrupted some shipments at China's third-largest port.

"We are monitoring the situation," a spokeswoman for the bank said.